<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 1216
                    The President to the Ambassador in
                        China (
                        Hurley
                    )Sent to the Commander, Naval Group,
                        China, via Navy channels.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1216</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1216</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-23T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-23T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1216" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1216">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/8–745: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1216<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the Ambassador in
                        China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HMGPJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1216fn1">Sent to the Commander, Naval Group,
                        China, via Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-23">23 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 310, personal and top secret, from the President for Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_HMGPJ1">Hurley</persName>.</p>
                <p>Please deliver the following message to Generalissimo <persName corresp="#p_CK1">Chiang Kai-shek</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I refer to your message of 19 [<hi rend="italic">20</hi>] July<note n="2" xml:id="d1216fn2">
                                <ref target="#d1214">Document No. 1214</ref>.</note> quoting your
                            telegram to <persName corresp="#p_SGIV1">Generalissimo
                            Stalin</persName>.</p>
                        <p>I asked that you carry out the Yalta agreement but I had not asked that
                            you make any concession in excess of that agreement. If you and
                                <persName corresp="#p_SGIV1">Generalissimo Stalin</persName> differ
                            as to the correct interpretation of the Yalta agreement, I hope you will
                            arrange for <persName corresp="#p_STV1">Soong</persName> to return to
                            Moscow and continue your efforts to reach complete understanding.
                                <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_THS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Truman</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
